sections.Trivia:
- WSG is based on the Olympic games, which they have every four years. The summer games which will be in 2024 will begin on Friday, July 26, and ends on Sunday, August 11.
- Chiemi Isojima's cat has the same character design as the stray cat in Welcome to Bocchan Restaurant.
- Locations shown in the advert at the beginnning of the episode include:
- Nagoya: Nagoya Castle, Nagoya TV Tower, Nagoya Oasis 21;
- Gifu Prefecture: Shirakawa-go, Gifu Castle, Hida Mountains;
- Nagano Prefecture: Matsumoto Castle, Zenkō-ji;
- Yamanashi Prefecture: Takeda Shrine, Oshino Hakkai;
- Kanagawa Prefecture: Great Buddha of Kōtoku-in, Yokohama Landmark Tower, Cosmo Clock 21;
- Tokyo: Tokyo Big Sight, Bell Tree Tower, Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building, Rainbow Bridge, Tokyo Station, Ginza, Kaminarimon, Tokyo Tower, Kanda Shrine.
- The sponsor for the Kamen Yaiba chocolate, Mitsuzuka, has a logo font similar to the one of the candy company Glico.
- One of the magazines in the bookstore is an imitation of Weekly Shōnen Sunday.
- The dishes eaten by the Mouri family at their home are Kinpira Gobo, miso soup and salted grilled fish (塩焼き 魚).
